WEBVTT

00:04.135 --> 00:06.107
AND THEY LIVED HAPPILY
 EVER AFTER.

00:06.107 --> 00:10.141
ONE MORE STORY, DAD,
 PLEASE?

00:10.141 --> 00:11.442
OKAY.

00:13.144 --> 00:15.216
ONCE UPON A TIME,
 THERE WERE THREE BEARS.

00:15.216 --> 00:17.648
NOW THERE´S LOTS OF THEM.
 GOOD NIGHT, MAX.

00:17.648 --> 00:20.521
HEY, GRANDPA´S ON THE PHONE.
 SAY HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

00:20.521 --> 00:22.223
HI, GRANDPA.
 HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

00:22.223 --> 00:24.655
THANKS FOR SENDING ME THOSE
 REALLY SMALL TWEEZERS.

00:26.157 --> 00:29.160
GRANDPA SAYS THOSE CAME WITH
 A WHOLE SWISS ARMY KNIFE.

00:29.160 --> 00:31.162
GIVE ME THE PHONE.

00:31.162 --> 00:33.534
HEY, DADDY,
 GEORGE WANTS TO SAY HI.

00:37.238 --> 00:38.569
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, VIC.

00:38.569 --> 00:40.711
I WAS GONNA SAY THANKS
 FOR THE SWISS ARMY KNIFE,

00:40.711 --> 00:43.214
BUT APPARENTLY YOU DIDN´T
 SEND IT TO ME. BYE.

00:43.214 --> 00:44.675
I GOTTA GO, DADDY.

00:44.675 --> 00:46.447
THE KIDS ARE GETTING READY
 FOR BED.

00:46.447 --> 00:47.578
BYE, GRANDPA!

00:47.578 --> 00:50.151
ALL RIGHT, MAX.
 LIGHTS OUT.

00:50.151 --> 00:53.424
I WISH GRANDPA DIDN´T LIVE
 SO FAR AWAY.

00:53.424 --> 00:55.426
YOU REALLY LOVE HIM,
 DON´T YOU?

00:55.426 --> 00:56.687
YEAH.

00:56.687 --> 01:00.461
YOU KNOW,
 IF MY DAD WERE ALIVE,

01:00.461 --> 01:03.694
HE COULD BEAT UP
 GRANDPA VIC.

01:03.694 --> 01:07.067
YOUR DAD WAS THE BEST DAD,
 HUH?

01:07.067 --> 01:09.200
DAMN STRAIGHT.

01:09.200 --> 01:12.203
AND I WAS THE MOST IMPORTANT
 THING IN HIS LIFE.

01:12.203 --> 01:15.546
GEORGE, TELL YOUR MAMA
 I´LL BE HOME AROUND 5:00,

01:15.546 --> 01:17.548
AND DON´T GIVE HER
 A HARD TIME.

01:17.548 --> 01:20.080
DAD, DO YOU HAVE TO GO
 TO WORK TODAY?

01:20.080 --> 01:23.814
SPORT, YOU KNOW IT´S MY FIRST
 DAY IN THE BIG LEAGUES.

01:23.814 --> 01:25.756
I MEAN, I CAN´T MISS --

01:27.618 --> 01:29.190
YOU KNOW WHAT?

01:29.190 --> 01:31.562
THE DODGERS CAN LIVE WITHOUT ME
 ONE MORE DAY.

01:31.562 --> 01:33.724
LET´S GO GRAB SOME
 OTTER POPS,

01:33.724 --> 01:36.096
WE´LL CATCH
 SOME EARLY SURFING,

01:36.096 --> 01:38.169
THEN WE´LL HEAD OVER TO
 DISNEYLAND.

01:38.169 --> 01:40.100
HEY, WHAT DO YOU SAY
 THIS TIME YOU DRIVE?

01:41.232 --> 01:43.204
DAD, YOU´RE A GOOD BASEBALL
 PLAYER.

01:43.204 --> 01:45.636
HOW COME YOU NEVER PLAYED
 IN THE BIG LEAGUES?

01:45.636 --> 01:48.779
WELL, NOBODY WANTED TO BE
 AN ATHLETE BACK THEN.

01:48.779 --> 01:51.442
KIDS IN MY DAY
 DREAMED ABOUT WORKING

01:51.442 --> 01:53.644
IN AN AIRPLANE-PARTS
 FACTORY.

01:55.386 --> 01:58.389
AND I´M LIVING THAT DREAM.

01:58.389 --> 01:59.690
WHAT ELSE DID GRANDPA DO?

01:59.690 --> 02:02.193
THE THING THAT AMAZED ME
 ABOUT YOUR GRANDPA

02:02.193 --> 02:04.795
WAS THAT HE COULD HANDLE
 ANY EMERGENCY.

02:06.126 --> 02:09.128
DAD! DAD!
 GILBERT´S NOT BREATHING!

02:10.261 --> 02:12.563
ALL RIGHT, GIVE HIM TO ME,
 SON.

02:24.415 --> 02:27.818
LIVE!

02:34.255 --> 02:36.857
HE SWALLOWED A MARBLE,
 SPORT.

02:38.429 --> 02:40.231
START KEEPING YOUR MARBLES

02:40.231 --> 02:44.265
IN THIS BRAND-NEW,
 PERSONALIZED MARBLE BAG.

02:44.265 --> 02:46.837
WOW!

02:46.837 --> 02:50.571
YOU GAVE ME THAT BAG,
 BUT IT DOESN´T SAY "GEORGE,"

02:50.571 --> 02:52.343
IT SAYS "CROWN ROYAL."

02:52.343 --> 02:58.178
THAT´S...
 BECAUSE I WAS HIS LITTLE KING.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.780
OH.

02:59.780 --> 03:02.653
BUT IT WASN´T JUST BASEBALL
 AND SAVING LIVES.

03:02.653 --> 03:05.856
MY DAD LOVED THE HOUSE
 TO BE FILLED WITH MUSIC.

03:11.792 --> 03:13.264
YOU KNOW, NEXT YEAR,

03:13.264 --> 03:15.596
WHEN YOUR HANDS
 ARE A LITTLE BIGGER,

03:15.596 --> 03:17.368
I´LL TEACH YOU TO PLAY.

03:17.368 --> 03:19.370
WHAT´S THAT SONG, DAD?

03:19.370 --> 03:23.474
IT´S JUST A LITTLE SOMETHING
 I WROTE

03:23.474 --> 03:25.936
CALLED "MY BOY GEORGE."

03:27.538 --> 03:30.911
HOW COME YOU NEVER WROTE A SONG
 CALLED "MY BOY MAX"?

03:30.911 --> 03:31.812
I DID.

03:31.812 --> 03:33.514
YOU HEAR IT ALL THE TIME.

03:33.514 --> 03:35.215
THEY JUST CHANGED THE WORDS.

03:35.215 --> 03:37.748
♫ IF YOU´RE HAPPY AND YOU KNOW
 IT, MY BOY MAX ♫

03:37.748 --> 03:38.919
[ CLAPS ]

03:38.919 --> 03:40.851
DAD.

03:40.851 --> 03:43.854
ALL RIGHT, I NEVER LEARNED
 TO PLAY.

03:43.854 --> 03:47.598
MY DAD DIED IN A CAR ACCIDENT
 THAT SUMMER.

03:47.598 --> 03:49.900
I WISH I HAD MET HIM.

03:52.503 --> 03:53.664
ME TOO, MAX.

03:53.664 --> 03:57.308
HE WAS THE GREATEST GUY
 IN THE WORLD.

03:59.910 --> 04:04.244
GEORGE,
 WHY DO YOU DO THAT?

04:04.244 --> 04:05.616
DO WHAT?

04:05.616 --> 04:07.548
EVERY TIME YOU TELL THESE
 STORIES ABOUT YOUR DAD,

04:07.548 --> 04:09.880
THEY´RE A LITTLE DIFFERENT.
 HE´S GONNA CATCH ON.

04:09.880 --> 04:11.522
AM I SUPPOSED TO TELL HIM

04:11.522 --> 04:13.684
THAT MY FATHER ABANDONED ME
 WHEN I WAS A BABY?

04:13.684 --> 04:15.356
WELL, IT´S THE TRUTH.

04:15.356 --> 04:18.589
ALL THESE FANTASTIC STORIES
 ARE GONNA BE HARD TO EXPLAIN

04:18.589 --> 04:22.563
WHEN HE GROWS UP AND FINDS OUT
 THAT YOUR FATHER WAS, YOU KNOW,

04:22.563 --> 04:25.866
AN UNEMPLOYED GAMBLER
 WHO WAS KILLED BY ALCOHOL.

04:25.866 --> 04:28.268
HE WASN´T KILLED BY ALCOHOL.

04:28.268 --> 04:30.401
HE WAS HIT BY A BEER TRUCK.

04:30.401 --> 04:33.404
I´M TELLING MAX ABOUT THE KIND
 OF FATHER I WISH I HAD,

04:33.404 --> 04:35.406
SOMEBODY
 HE COULD BE PROUD OF.

04:35.406 --> 04:39.450
GEORGE, HE´S GOT SOMEBODY
 TO BE PROUD OF.

04:39.450 --> 04:40.551
HE´S GOT YOU.

04:40.551 --> 04:42.453
AND THAT´S ENOUGH.

04:42.453 --> 04:43.614
YOU REALLY THINK SO?

04:43.614 --> 04:45.015
YES.

04:45.015 --> 04:47.788
YOU´RE A GOOD ROLE MODEL,
 YOU´RE HARDWORKING.

04:47.788 --> 04:50.521
WAIT A SECOND.
 I´M NOT PLAYING THIS GAME.

04:50.521 --> 04:51.862
BUT IT´S A GOOD GAME.

04:51.862 --> 04:54.395
AND THE WINNER GETS TO GET BUSY
 WITH ME.

04:54.395 --> 04:58.369
OH, I DON´T KNOW IF I FEEL
 LIKE GETTING BUSY TONIGHT.

04:58.369 --> 05:00.731
YOU KNOW,
 I JUST DON´T FEEL CUTE

05:00.731 --> 05:02.373
AND I DON´T LOOK THAT SEXY.

05:02.373 --> 05:04.535
YES, YOU DO.
 YOU ALWAYS LOOK HOT.

05:04.535 --> 05:05.836
NOW YOU´RE DOING IT.

05:07.007 --> 05:10.441
[ INTRO TO WAR´S "LOW RIDER"
 PLAYS ]

05:20.591 --> 05:26.397
♫ ALL MY FRIENDS
 KNOW THE LOW RIDER ♫

05:28.399 --> 05:33.604
♫ THE LOW RIDER
 IS A LITTLE HIGHER ♫

05:54.354 --> 05:55.886
[ SCOFFS ]

05:55.886 --> 05:58.559
I TOLD YOU, THE MONEY IN THE
 FOUNTAIN DOESN´T BELONG TO YOU.

05:58.559 --> 06:00.090
IT´S FOR WISHES.

06:00.090 --> 06:03.363
BUT MY WISH WAS TO GET
 ALL THE MONEY IN THE FOUNTAIN.

06:03.363 --> 06:04.995
EXCUSE ME.

06:06.497 --> 06:08.439
WHAT´S WRONG
 WITH YOUR DOG?

06:10.571 --> 06:13.744
HE´S "SICK."

06:13.744 --> 06:15.476
SHOULDN´T HE BE
 AT THE VET?

06:16.877 --> 06:18.649
OH, NO.
 I KNOW HOW THAT WORKS.

06:18.649 --> 06:20.711
I GIVE YOU MONEY, BUT INSTEAD
 OF GETTING MEDICAL CARE,

06:20.711 --> 06:22.483
YOU GO OUT AND BUY BOOZE.

06:22.483 --> 06:25.656
MOM, PLEASE DON´T DO THIS!
 YOU´RE HARASSING A HOMELESS GUY!

06:25.656 --> 06:28.388
IS THAT BIG BOX
 YOUR HOUSE?

06:28.388 --> 06:29.860
LUCKY.

06:29.860 --> 06:33.393
WHERE IS THE WATER AND SHELTER
 FOR THIS ANIMAL?

06:33.393 --> 06:37.928
IT´S IN MY VACATION BOX
 AT THE BEACH.

06:37.928 --> 06:39.900
I´LL GIVE YOU $20 FOR HIM.

06:39.900 --> 06:41.502
ARE YOU SERIOUS? TAKE HIM.

06:41.502 --> 06:43.103
I CAN´T BELIEVE
 YOU´RE DOING THIS.

06:43.103 --> 06:45.576
WHY DO YOU HAVE TO GET INVOLVED
 WITH EVERY LOST CAUSE?

06:45.576 --> 06:49.440
THIS DOG IS NOT A LOST CAUSE.
 LOOK AT HIM!

06:49.440 --> 06:51.181
I JUST WANT TO HUG HIM!

06:51.181 --> 06:52.543
EEW.

06:53.413 --> 06:54.585
THANK YOU!

06:54.585 --> 06:56.547
MOM, WHAT DO YOU THINK
 HIS NAME IS?

06:56.547 --> 06:57.788
I DON´T KNOW, SWEETHEART.

06:57.788 --> 07:00.721
WE CAN CALL HIM
 ANYTHING WE WANT.

07:00.721 --> 07:03.954
GOODBYE, STINKY BOX MAN!

07:05.556 --> 07:07.197
I LOVE STORES LIKE THIS!

07:07.197 --> 07:10.601
OOH, FIVE GALLONS
 OF MAYONNAISE FOR $5!

07:10.601 --> 07:14.434
THIS JAR IS SO BIG, WHEN I´M
 DONE, THEY CAN BURY ME IN IT.

07:14.434 --> 07:17.968
MOM, YOU HAVEN´T BEEN FIVE
 GALLONS SINCE YOU WERE 20.

07:17.968 --> 07:19.610
HEY, GEORGE!
 HEY, ERNIE!

07:19.610 --> 07:20.971
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

07:20.971 --> 07:23.774
MY MOM WANTED TO SEE
 THE NEW BUYER´S WAREHOUSE.

07:23.774 --> 07:25.015
YEAH, MINE TOO.

07:25.015 --> 07:26.917
ARE WE PATHETIC OR WHAT?

07:26.917 --> 07:29.449
HEY, GEORGE IS ONLY HERE
 TO REACH THE HIGH STUFF.

07:29.449 --> 07:33.183
YOU´RE HERE BECAUSE YOU STILL
 LIVE WITH YOUR MOM, YOU FREAK.

07:33.183 --> 07:35.656
HEY, I´M NOT
 JUST HERE SHOPPING.

07:35.656 --> 07:37.157
I´M SCOPING OUT THE LADIES.

07:37.157 --> 07:39.990
I´M GONNA BUY YOU UNDERWEAR.
 HOLD MY PURSE.

07:42.462 --> 07:43.864
NICE PURSE, NEW UNDERWEAR.

07:43.864 --> 07:45.766
I THINK
 I´M FALLING FOR YOU.

07:45.766 --> 07:47.498
SHEE-OW!

07:47.498 --> 07:48.599
SHUT UP!

07:51.471 --> 07:53.644
This way, this way,
 this way!

07:53.644 --> 07:54.745
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

07:54.745 --> 07:55.946
Turn this around!

07:55.946 --> 07:57.878
We gotta leave.
 Leave right now!

07:57.878 --> 07:59.510
WHO´S THAT?
 NOBODY.

07:59.510 --> 08:00.611
COME WITH ME NOW,
 OR I´M LEAVING WITHOUT YOU.

08:01.882 --> 08:03.253
OH, MY GOD.

08:03.253 --> 08:04.615
BENNY?

08:04.615 --> 08:06.486
BENNY LOPEZ?

08:12.222 --> 08:15.966
I´VE NEVER SEEN MY MOTHER
 RUN FROM SOMEBODY BEFORE.

08:15.966 --> 08:18.529
YOUR MOTHER?

08:18.529 --> 08:20.771
GEORGIE LOPEZ!

08:20.771 --> 08:24.504
OH, IT´S BEEN SO LONG!

08:24.504 --> 08:28.038
WHOA, HOW DRUNK WAS I?

08:28.038 --> 08:29.910
YOU LOOK
 JUST LIKE YOUR DAD.

08:29.910 --> 08:31.942
I´D KNOW THAT BIG HEAD
 ANYWHERE.

08:31.942 --> 08:33.683
YOU KNEW MY DAD?!

08:33.683 --> 08:36.145
OF COURSE I KNEW YOUR DAD.
 HE´S MY BROTHER.

08:36.145 --> 08:38.217
I´M YOUR AUNT CECELIA.

08:38.217 --> 08:40.220
I HAVEN´T SEEN YOU
 SINCE YOU WERE A BABY.

08:40.220 --> 08:43.594
MY MOM NEVER TOLD ME
 I HAD AN AUNT.

08:43.594 --> 08:44.895
I´M NOT SURPRISED.

08:44.895 --> 08:48.599
BUT I DID SEND YOU GIFTS
 ON YOUR BIRTHDAY.

08:48.599 --> 08:50.030
OH, MY GOD!

08:50.030 --> 08:51.962
YOU´RE THE POISON-COOKIE
 LADY!

08:51.962 --> 08:54.204
I HAVE SO MANY QUESTIONS
 ABOUT MY DAD.

08:54.204 --> 08:56.206
HE DIED
 WHEN I WAS SO YOUNG.

08:56.206 --> 08:57.137
DIED?

08:57.137 --> 08:59.770
MANNY ISN´T DEAD.

08:59.770 --> 09:02.042
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

09:02.042 --> 09:05.315
I LOST TOUCH WITH HIM A COUPLE
 OF YEARS AGO, BUT LAST I HEARD,

09:05.315 --> 09:07.748
HE WAS LIVING SOMEWHERE
 IN NORTHERN CALIFORNIA.

09:07.748 --> 09:12.723
SO YOU´RE SAYING MY MOM´S
 BEEN LYING TO ME MY WHOLE LIFE?

09:12.723 --> 09:14.184
GEORGE! GEORGE!

09:14.184 --> 09:16.156
FANTASTIC NEWS!

09:18.889 --> 09:21.231
ERNIE, THIS IS MY AUNT.

09:21.231 --> 09:24.765
SHE JUST TOLD ME
 MY DAD´S ALIVE.

09:24.765 --> 09:28.739
OKAY, I GOT
 RELATIVELY GOOD NEWS.

09:36.346 --> 09:38.248
WHAT DID
 THE DOCTOR SAY, MOM?

09:38.248 --> 09:40.010
WHAT DOES HE HAVE?

09:40.010 --> 09:43.083
IT´D BE EASIER TO TELL YOU
 WHAT HE DOESN´T HAVE.

09:43.083 --> 09:44.815
THIS IS DOG IS DIABETIC,

09:44.815 --> 09:47.788
HE HAS KIDNEY STONES,
 ARTHRITIS, CATARACTS,

09:47.788 --> 09:51.321
AND SOMETHING CALLED
 "ERUPTING TAIL ACNE."

09:51.321 --> 09:52.923
MOM, HOW DO I SAY THIS...

09:52.923 --> 09:54.795
BLAH!

09:54.795 --> 09:58.328
CARMEN, THE LITTLE GUY MAY BE
 SICK, BUT WE BROUGHT HIM HOME,

09:58.328 --> 10:01.371
AND NOW IT´S OUR JOB
 TO NURSE HIM BACK TO HEALTH.

10:01.371 --> 10:04.905
HE DESERVES ALL THE LOVE
 AND AFFECTION THAT WE CAN GIVE.

10:04.905 --> 10:07.938
DON´T TOUCH HIM!!

10:07.938 --> 10:10.240
I CAN´T TOUCH OUR DOG?

10:10.240 --> 10:11.982
OF COURSE YOU CAN, HONEY.

10:11.982 --> 10:13.283
BUT HE´S GOT MANGE.

10:13.283 --> 10:14.945
YOU JUST HAVE TO USE...

10:14.945 --> 10:16.917
UH...

10:16.917 --> 10:18.218
THE PETTING STICK.

10:18.218 --> 10:19.850
GO AHEAD, USE THAT.

10:21.852 --> 10:24.254
ANGIE, I GOTTA TALK TO YOU.
 KIDS, GO OUTSIDE.

10:24.254 --> 10:25.295
WHAT´S THAT SMELL?

10:25.295 --> 10:26.957
IT´S OUR NEW DOG!

10:26.957 --> 10:28.899
HE DOESN´T SMELL NEW.

10:28.899 --> 10:31.401
I KNOW YOU DON´T WANT A DOG, BUT
 HE WAS LIVING ON THE STREET --

10:31.401 --> 10:33.163
NO, NO. CAN WE
 TALK ABOUT THIS LATER?

10:33.163 --> 10:34.965
GET HIS LEASH
 AND TAKE HIM FOR A WALK.

10:34.965 --> 10:36.737
HE CAN´T WALK.

10:36.737 --> 10:39.069
OKAY, THEN TAKE HIM OUTSIDE
 AND SQUEEZE HIM TILL HE PEES.

10:39.069 --> 10:41.712
OH!

10:41.712 --> 10:44.214
BUT TAKE THIS STRAINER IN CASE
 HE PASSES A KIDNEY STONE.

10:48.078 --> 10:49.419
SO WHAT´S GOING ON?

10:49.419 --> 10:51.782
ANGIE, MY FATHER´S ALIVE.
 WHAT?

10:51.782 --> 10:53.383
HE´S ALIVE.
 MY MOM LIED TO ME.

10:53.383 --> 10:54.654
ARE YOU KIDDING?

10:54.654 --> 10:55.886
NO. I MET MY DAD´S SISTER.

10:55.886 --> 10:58.058
SHE TOLD ME HE´S IN
 NORTHERN CALIFORNIA.

10:58.058 --> 10:59.059
WHAT DOES YOUR MOM SAY?

10:59.059 --> 11:00.390
SHE DIDN´T SAY ANYTHING.

11:00.390 --> 11:02.132
SHE RAN OUT AS SOON
 AS SHE SAW MY AUNT.

11:02.132 --> 11:04.865
HOW CRAZY IS THIS?

11:04.865 --> 11:07.968
I NEVER THOUGHT I´D BE ABLE
 TO TALK TO HIM OR...

11:07.968 --> 11:10.941
SEE HIM WITH MY OWN EYES.

11:10.941 --> 11:13.003
NOW IT COULD HAPPEN.

11:13.003 --> 11:14.745
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

11:17.347 --> 11:19.009
[ SIGHS ]

11:22.813 --> 11:24.915
EXCUSE ME,
 ARE YOU MANNY LOPEZ?

11:24.915 --> 11:26.156
YES.

11:26.156 --> 11:27.217
I´M --

11:27.217 --> 11:29.790
GEORGIE! MY LITTLE BOY!

11:32.022 --> 11:34.024
MOM TOLD ME YOU WERE DEAD!

11:34.024 --> 11:35.766
SHE TOLD ME YOU WERE DEAD!

11:37.327 --> 11:39.930
I GUESS I WON´T BE
 NEEDING THIS ANYMORE.

11:39.930 --> 11:42.302
MY PRAYERS
 HAVE BEEN ANSWERED!

11:49.039 --> 11:50.811
I THINK I WANT TO SEE HIM.

11:50.811 --> 11:52.843
HONEY, I´M NOT SURE
 THAT´S A GOOD IDEA.

11:52.843 --> 11:55.185
YOU REALLY DON´T KNOW
 ANYTHING ABOUT THIS GUY.

11:55.185 --> 11:56.486
WHAT IF HE TURNS OUT TO BE

11:56.486 --> 11:58.749
SOMEBODY YOU DON´T WANT
 IN YOUR LIFE?

12:01.922 --> 12:05.395
DID YOU CALL THE COPS
 ON ME AGAIN?!

12:05.395 --> 12:09.129
LOOK, WE´RE JUST HAVING A LITTLE
 FAMILY SQUABBLE, OKAY?

12:09.129 --> 12:10.200
I´M NOT THE POLICE!

12:10.200 --> 12:12.062
THEN WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

12:12.062 --> 12:13.904
I´M GEORGE, YOUR SON!

12:13.904 --> 12:15.966
HOLY CRAP.

12:15.966 --> 12:19.009
WHAT DOES SOMEBODY HAVE TO DO
 TO GET AWAY FROM YOU?

12:21.972 --> 12:24.815
WOW, ANGIE,
 THIS IS MESSED UP.

12:24.815 --> 12:27.077
I DON´T THINK
 YOU SHOULD LOOK FOR HIM.

12:27.077 --> 12:28.278
THAT´S EASY FOR YOU TO SAY.

12:28.278 --> 12:29.950
YOU HAD A FATHER
 YOUR WHOLE LIFE.

12:29.950 --> 12:31.822
I DON´T WANT YOU
 TO GET HURT.

12:31.822 --> 12:33.954
WHOEVER HE IS, MY MOTHER
 SHOULD´VE TOLD ME ABOUT HIM.

12:33.954 --> 12:35.956
WHO KNOWS WHAT ELSE
 SHE´S LIED TO ME ABOUT?

12:35.956 --> 12:38.959
MAYBE SANTA CLAUS
 DOES LIKE MEXICAN KIDS!

12:44.895 --> 12:48.198
ERNIE, YOU SEEN MY MOM? SHE
 DITCHED CARPOOL THIS MORNING.

12:48.198 --> 12:54.074
NO, I CAN´T SEE ANYTHING BUT THE
 FUTURE MRS. ERNESTO CARDENAS.

12:54.074 --> 12:55.375
WHO´S THAT?

12:55.375 --> 12:57.147
I DON´T KNOW.

12:57.147 --> 12:58.408
BUT I´LL TELL YOU THIS --

12:58.408 --> 13:01.081
I´D KILL YOU FOR HER.

13:08.788 --> 13:09.990
HI, YOU MUST BE GEORGE.

13:09.990 --> 13:11.321
I´M YOUR NEW
 ASSISTANT MANAGER.

13:11.321 --> 13:12.792
BILL POWERS HIRED ME.

13:12.792 --> 13:14.995
YOU MUST BE
 SOMEBODY PRETTY SPECIAL

13:14.995 --> 13:17.197
TO GET THE OWNER OF
 THE COMPANY´S ATTENTION, MISS...

13:17.197 --> 13:18.999
POWERS. CAMPBELL POWERS.

13:18.999 --> 13:21.531
YOU CHANGED YOUR NAME
 TO THE OWNER´S LAST NAME.

13:21.531 --> 13:23.033
YOU REALLY ARE
 A TEAM PLAYER!

13:23.033 --> 13:24.404
I´M THE OWNER´S NIECE,

13:24.404 --> 13:26.877
BUT I DON´T WANT ANYONE
 TO BE THREATENED BY THAT.

13:26.877 --> 13:27.537
I´M QUALIFIED.

13:27.537 --> 13:29.179
I WENT TO SCHOOL.

13:29.179 --> 13:33.343
THIS IS MY B.A. FROM UCLA,
 AND MY MBA FROM PEPPERDINE.

13:33.343 --> 13:35.145
I GOT A PLAQUE, TOO.

13:37.287 --> 13:38.919
MINE SINGS.

13:38.919 --> 13:44.154
♫ WAY DOWN
 UPON THE SWANEE RIVER ♫

13:44.154 --> 13:49.029
♫ FAR, FAR AWAY ♫

13:49.029 --> 13:51.031
I GOTTA GET OUT OF HERE,
 BUT MAKE YOURSELF AT HOME.

13:51.031 --> 13:52.502
I´M SURE YOU GOT
 A LOT TO DO,

13:52.502 --> 13:54.004
FILLING OUT PAPERWORK,
 SETTING UP E-MAILS --

13:54.004 --> 13:56.206
DID IT.
 CAME IN AT 6:00.

13:56.206 --> 13:57.237
OH.

13:57.237 --> 13:59.139
I STILL WANT TO LEAVE.

13:59.139 --> 14:00.911
HEY, MOM.

14:00.911 --> 14:02.442
I´M WORKING.
 WHAT DO YOU WANT?

14:02.442 --> 14:04.274
I DON´T KNOW.
 CUP OF COFFEE, A MUFFIN...

14:04.274 --> 14:07.047
A REASON WHY YOU TOLD ME MY DAD
 WAS DEAD FOR 36 YEARS?

14:07.047 --> 14:09.279
HERE´S A MUFFIN.
 ONE OUT OF THREE AIN´T BAD.

14:09.279 --> 14:11.221
OH, NO.

14:11.221 --> 14:13.023
I TRIED TO CALL YOU LAST NIGHT,
 AND YOU DUCKED ME THIS MORNING.

14:13.023 --> 14:15.155
YOU´RE NOT WALKING AWAY.
 WE´RE GONNA TALK ABOUT THIS NOW.

14:15.155 --> 14:18.188
REALLY? WHAT ARE YOU
 GONNA DO ABOUT IT, HIT ME?

14:18.188 --> 14:19.189
COME ON.

14:19.189 --> 14:21.231
HIT ME.

14:21.231 --> 14:22.862
MOM, YOU´RE A CRAZY PERSON.

14:22.862 --> 14:24.895
YOU´D RATHER FIGHT ME
 THAN TELL ME THE TRUTH.

14:24.895 --> 14:26.536
LET´S TAKE THIS OUTSIDE.

14:26.536 --> 14:29.869
I DON´T WANT TO EMBARRASS YOU
 IN FRONT OF YOUR LITTLE FRIENDS.

14:29.869 --> 14:31.942
ALL I WANT
 IS A STRAIGHT ANSWER.

14:31.942 --> 14:34.204
WHY DIDN´T YOU TELL ME
 MY FATHER WAS ALIVE?

14:34.204 --> 14:35.245
IT WAS
 NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

14:35.245 --> 14:36.606
NONE OF MY BUSINESS?!

14:36.606 --> 14:39.379
WHY YOU GOT A PAIR
 OF MEN´S SHOES IN YOUR TRUNK

14:39.379 --> 14:41.011
IS NONE OF MY BUSINESS.

14:41.011 --> 14:44.084
HOW YOU GOT A "TUPAC LIVES"
 BUMPER STICKER ON YOUR CAR

14:44.084 --> 14:45.385
IS NONE OF MY BUSINESS.

14:45.385 --> 14:47.587
NOT LETTING ME KNOW
 I HAVE A FATHER --

14:47.587 --> 14:49.089
I THINK THAT´S MY BUSINESS.

14:49.089 --> 14:50.590
I HAD A RIGHT TO KNOW!

14:50.590 --> 14:53.493
OKAY. HOW WOULD YOU GET
 A FOUR-YEAR-OLD TO STOP ASKING

14:53.493 --> 14:55.495
"WHERE´S MY DADDY?
 WHERE´S MY DADDY?"

14:55.495 --> 14:59.099
AFTER THE THOUSANDTH TIME,
 YOU SAY, "YOUR FATHER´S DEAD."

14:59.099 --> 15:00.600
I´M NOT FOUR ANYMORE.

15:00.600 --> 15:02.372
I DESERVE AN ANSWER.

15:02.372 --> 15:04.104
FINE.

15:04.104 --> 15:05.435
WHERE´S MY DAD?

15:05.435 --> 15:07.437
HE´S DEAD.
 AREN´T YOU GLAD WE DID THIS?

15:09.980 --> 15:11.381
YOU KNOW WHAT?
 I´M GONNA FIND HIM.

15:11.381 --> 15:12.542
SURE, YOU GO LOOK FOR HIM.

15:12.542 --> 15:14.114
YOU KNOW WHAT
 YOU´RE GONNA FIND?

15:14.114 --> 15:16.246
A MAN WHO DOESN´T
 GIVE A DAMN ABOUT YOU.

15:16.246 --> 15:18.949
YOU DON´T KNOW THAT.

15:18.949 --> 15:22.222
HE NEVER LOVED YOU.
 HE NEVER EVEN HELD YOU.

15:26.126 --> 15:28.999
GEORGE, I KNOW
 THIS ISN´T A GOOD TIME,

15:28.999 --> 15:32.232
BUT I CAN´T GET THAT
 RUBBER FISH TO STOP SINGING.

15:32.232 --> 15:35.265
I´M SORRY, CAMPBELL, I CAN´T
 DEAL WITH THAT RIGHT NOW!

15:35.265 --> 15:36.506
I GOT THINGS TO SORT OUT!

15:36.506 --> 15:41.271
♫ SADLY I ROAM ♫

15:41.271 --> 15:44.114
♫ STILL LONGING
 FOR THE OLD PLANTATION ♫

15:44.114 --> 15:45.976
STILL FUNNY.

15:49.049 --> 15:51.051
OKAY, I´M GONNA SHOW EVERYBODY

15:51.051 --> 15:53.653
HOW TO GIVE THE DOG
 HIS INSULIN SHOT.

15:53.653 --> 15:55.385
[ SIGHS ]

15:58.558 --> 16:01.191
YOU KNOW,
 WE LEARN THROUGH DOING.

16:01.191 --> 16:02.592
YOU GIVE HIM THE SHOT.

16:02.592 --> 16:05.695
HERE, YOU´RE A BOY.
 YOU´RE GROSS, YOU DO IT.

16:05.695 --> 16:06.596
I´M JUST A KID.

16:06.596 --> 16:06.966
I´M NOT DOING IT.

16:09.569 --> 16:13.103
GEORGE, I CALLED AND YOU LEFT
 WORK TWO HOURS AGO.

16:13.103 --> 16:14.344
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

16:14.344 --> 16:15.705
YEAH.

16:15.705 --> 16:18.578
JUST BEEN DRIVING AROUND
 FOR A WHILE, THINKING.

16:20.180 --> 16:22.552
AND EATING.
 AND THINKING.

16:23.983 --> 16:27.417
I´M NOT GONNA LOOK
 FOR MY DAD.

16:27.417 --> 16:29.119
ARE YOU SURE?

16:29.119 --> 16:31.191
I TALKED TO MY MOM,
 AND, FOR ONCE, SHE MADE SENSE.

16:31.191 --> 16:33.663
THE GUY LEFT, AND HE HAD
 ALL THESE YEARS TO FIND ME.

16:33.663 --> 16:35.725
IF HE DOESN´T CARE ABOUT ME,
 WHY SHOULD I CARE ABOUT HIM?

16:37.227 --> 16:39.729
MOM, I CAN´T JUST CAN´T
 GIVE THE DOG A SHOT.

16:39.729 --> 16:42.172
I CAN´T BE AROUND
 YOU PANSIES.

16:44.734 --> 16:46.606
GEORGE, THE DOG
 NEEDS HIS INSULIN.

16:46.606 --> 16:49.079
IF HE DOESN´T GET IT,
 HE´LL GO INTO A COMA.

16:49.079 --> 16:52.412
[ SCOFFS ]
 WHAT´S HE IN NOW?

16:58.588 --> 17:00.490
EH!
 [ ALL CHEERING ]

17:00.490 --> 17:02.352
I´M PRETTY GOOD AT THIS!

17:02.352 --> 17:04.694
YOU KIDS WANT A SHOT?
 WHOA!

17:14.233 --> 17:15.734
HELLO, BENITA.

17:15.734 --> 17:17.707
CECELIA.

17:17.707 --> 17:20.140
IT´S BEEN A LONG TIME.

17:20.140 --> 17:22.142
UH-HUH.

17:22.142 --> 17:24.544
LET ME IN, BENNY.

17:24.544 --> 17:26.776
MAKE ME.

17:26.776 --> 17:27.646
OKAY.

17:27.646 --> 17:29.549
COME ON IN, CECELIA.

17:29.549 --> 17:31.281
IT´S BEEN OVER 30 YEARS.

17:31.281 --> 17:34.554
YOU HAVEN´T GOT ONE NICE THING
 TO SAY TO EACH OTHER?

17:37.287 --> 17:39.829
IT WAS WORTH A TRY.

17:39.829 --> 17:42.462
CECELIA, YOU WANT TO STAY
 FOR DINNER?

17:42.462 --> 17:43.763
I´M NOT GONNA STAY.

17:43.763 --> 17:46.566
I WAS JUST GOING THROUGH
 SOME OLD THINGS,

17:46.566 --> 17:49.469
AND I FOUND THESE PICTURES
 OF YOUR FATHER.

17:49.469 --> 17:51.741
I THOUGHT
 YOU MIGHT WANT THEM.

17:59.549 --> 18:02.182
WHO´S HE HOLDING?

18:02.182 --> 18:03.713
THAT´S YOU.

18:15.125 --> 18:16.866
THAT´S ME.

18:18.168 --> 18:20.330
YOU KNOW WHY
 HE´S HOLDING YOU?

18:20.330 --> 18:23.873
BECAUSE HE JUST TRADED IN
 YOUR CRIB FOR SOME WEED.

18:25.535 --> 18:27.207
I´M GONNA FIND HIM.

18:31.211 --> 18:32.742
WHAT DO YOU GOT THERE?

18:32.742 --> 18:35.815
MY AUNT CECELIA
 BROUGHT SOME PICTURES BY.

18:35.815 --> 18:37.817
THAT´S MY DAD HOLDING ME.

18:41.521 --> 18:44.354
YOU HAVE HIS SMILE.

18:44.354 --> 18:45.825
I DO, DON´T I?

18:57.607 --> 18:59.909
YOU COULDN´T
 SLEEP EITHER, HUH?

18:59.909 --> 19:03.713
YEAH, YOU AND ME, WE´VE BOTH
 GOT A LOT GOING ON INSIDE.

19:03.713 --> 19:06.646
I GOT THESE MIXED FEELINGS
 ABOUT MY DAD,

19:06.646 --> 19:09.749
YOU GOT RINGWORM
 AND A BLADDER INFECTION.

19:11.781 --> 19:14.924
TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH,
 I´M KIND OF NERVOUS.

19:14.924 --> 19:18.258
I MEAN, WHAT´S GONNA HAPPEN
 IF I FIND HIM?

19:18.258 --> 19:21.491
IS HE GONNA BE HAPPY
 TO SEE ME?

19:21.491 --> 19:24.294
IS HE GONNA BE PROUD OF ME?

19:26.436 --> 19:28.698
YOU KNOW, YOU´RE ALL RIGHT.

19:28.698 --> 19:30.440
YOU´RE A GOOD LISTENER.

19:30.440 --> 19:33.943
IT´S LIKE YOU UNDERSTAND
 EXACTLY WHAT I´M SAYING,

19:33.943 --> 19:36.776
LIKE YOU´RE FOLLOWING
 MY EVERY WORD.

19:40.410 --> 19:42.682
OKAY, I´LL TELL YOU WHAT --
 YOU CAN HAVE SOME SALAMI,

19:42.682 --> 19:44.454
BUT YOU´RE GONNA
 HAVE TO COME AND GET IT.

19:44.454 --> 19:46.356
YOU CAN DO IT, DUDE.

19:46.356 --> 19:47.957
I BELIEVE IN YOU.

19:47.957 --> 19:49.188
COME ON.

19:49.188 --> 19:51.961
COME ON.

19:51.961 --> 19:54.564
DON´T MAKE ME GET THE SHOVEL.

19:54.564 --> 19:57.327
DON´T MAKE ME GET THE SHOVEL.

19:57.327 --> 19:59.969
COME ON, BOY.

19:59.969 --> 20:01.971
COME ON!

20:01.971 --> 20:04.203
COME ON!

20:04.203 --> 20:06.236
COME ON!

20:06.236 --> 20:08.308
GOOD BOY.

20:09.679 --> 20:12.342
YOU JUST NEEDED
 A LITTLE MOTIVATION.

20:12.342 --> 20:15.645
I LEARNED THAT SHOVEL THING
 FROM MY MOM.

20:20.720 --> 20:29.529
♫ FAR FROM THE OLD FOLKS
 AT HOME ♫

20:29.529 --> 20:31.361
YOU KNOW,

20:31.361 --> 20:34.564
IF FISH COULD SING, THAT´S
 EXACTLY WHAT THEY´D SOUND LIKE.

20:34.564 --> 20:37.607
LISTEN, MAN, I GOT TO GET HOME
 TO ANGIE AND THE KIDS.

20:37.607 --> 20:39.269
YEAH, ME TOO.

20:39.269 --> 20:41.741
I GOTTA TAKE MY MOM TO HER
 DOCTOR´S APPOINTMENT.

20:41.741 --> 20:43.843
ONE MORE TIME?

20:46.476 --> 20:47.877
♫ WAY DOWN UPON... ♫
